description.narrative:
The strategic plan is focused on directing ECO-V to become the most recognized voluntary environmental organization dedicated to empower people to take action on climate change, sustainable living and biodiversity conservation to make&nbsp;Sri Lanka a better place for all living organisms by 2020. ECO-V, 2 year program is to create the necessary foundation to implement the strategic direction. This initiative comes under the intervention area - Sustainable development and climate justice. &nbsp;
Lack of understanding and awareness on how we (human beings) are interlinked with the nature around us has resulted in our exploitation and destruction not only of our surroundings and but also ourselves. ECO-V aims to bring about a better understanding and improve lives while also creating and promoting coexistence. Though conscious consumerism and following the 10 R process (Reject, Refuse, Reduce, Reuse, Repair, Replace, Recycle, Rethink, Remember and Repeat) ECO-V is promoting healthier living and alternative life style.
Program engages with right holders, duty bearers and policy makers on critical issues relating to conservation, sustainability and waste management. Programming will be implemented island wide. Private sector and organisations are encouraged to establish urban or balcony gardens to promote biodiversity within an urban setting thereby advocating interconnectedness while promoting an organic eco-centric approach to conservation and better living. Youth engaged through the Yathra (bicycle parades) educate and demonstrate the eco-centric approach creates a volunteer culture to protect and conserve the environment even beyond the program period.
Mainstreaming components are environment, conflict and gender.
